	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I use <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=174236#p174236" class="postlink">Pently</a>, an NES music engine whose <a href="https://github.com/Qix-/pently/blob/master/docs/pentlyas.md" class="postlink">input format</a> is based on MML and LilyPond. The tools are in Python, so they'll work on both Windows and Linux.<br /><br />Otherwise, if you use Linux on x86 (or Linux on x86-64 with 32-bit libraries installed), you can use Windows tools in Wine.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

