	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">How can tracks be kept in sync like this?</div><br />This feature is when you do not want to tracks to be kept in sync obviously. This happens rarely, but if you want to do it, you can. With a tracker you can't.<br /><br />The most obvious use is to include sound effects such as birds tweet in a music, and you don't want your birds tweet exactly at the same place in music every loop for instance. Not useful on NES, but definitely useful on platform with more sound channels.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
